KnownLibraries.Name: I2S
KnownLibraries.Author: Arduino
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Enables the communication with devices that use the Inter-IC Sound (I2S) Bus. Specific implementation for Arduino Zero.

KnownLibraries.Name: USBHost
KnownLibraries.Author: Arduino
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Allows the communication with USB peripherals like mice, keyboards, and thumbdrives. For Arduino MKR1000 and Zero.
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: The USBHost library allows the board to appear as a USB host, enabling it to communicate with peripherals like USB mice and keyboards. USBHost does not support devices that are connected through USB hubs. This includes some keyboards that have an internal hub.

KnownLibraries.Name: Wire
KnownLibraries.Author: Jonathan BAUDIN, Thibaut VIARD, Arduino
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Allows the communication between devices or sensors connected via Two Wire Interface Bus. Specific implementation for Arduino Zero.

KnownLibraries.Name: HID
KnownLibraries.Author: Arduino
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Module for PluggableUSB infrastructure. Exposes an API for devices like Keyboards, Mice and Gamepads

KnownLibraries.Name: SAMD_AnalogCorrection
KnownLibraries.Author: Arduino
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Sets and enables the digital correction logic of the SAMD ADC.
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: Useful to correct the values returned by the ADC.

KnownLibraries.Name: SDU
KnownLibraries.Author: Arduino
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Update the sketch on your board from an SD card

KnownLibraries.Name: SPI
KnownLibraries.Author: Jonathan BAUDIN, Thibaut VIARD, Arduino
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Enables the communication with devices that use the Serial Peripheral Interface (SPI) Bus. Specific implementation for Arduino Zero.
